  "text": "With the rapid development of wireless communication demands, the SDR platform has become a preferred approach to support multiple communication standards. The basic SDR receiver features an ultra-high speed analog-to-digital converter (ADC) for direct sampling and a software radio [CITATION_1] , leaving the downconversion to be done in digital domain. However, direct sampling ADCs featured in SDR receivers require high dynamic range and high sampling rate, which lead to unacceptable large power consumption for mobile applications. The structure shown in Fig. 1 incorporating LNA and mixer provides a more compatible approach to implementing mobile SDR receiver, which achieves a better balance between performance and power consumption.",
  "correct_citation": {
